<LP>
   AMCA INTERNATIONAL Ltd. shareholders at the annual meeting
approved a 1-for-5 consolidation of common shares and
changing the name of the diversified industrial company to
United Dominion Industries Ltd., both effective June 4.
Following the consolidation, the Charlotte, N.C., company
will have about 27 million common shares outstanding. AMCA is
55.4%-held by Canadian Pacific Ltd. a Montreal-based resource
and transportation company.
